==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic (perhaps in turn from Indo-European ''*ghabh-'', source of Latin [[habere]]).  Cognate with Old Frisian [[jeva]], Old High German [[geban]] (German [[geben]]), Old Saxon ''geƀan'' (Dutch [[geven]]), Old Norse [[gefa]] (Swedish [[giva]]), Gothic [[𐌲𐌹𐌱𐌰𐌽]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'jievan/

===Verb===
'''ġiefan''' (strong verb class V: '''ġiefþ''' ‘he gives’; '''ġeaf''' ‘he gave’; '''ġēafon''' ‘they gave’; '''ġeġiefen''' ‘given’)
# to [[give]]


